paragraphs.title: TF/IDF Featurizer
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.{HashingTF, IDF, Tokenizer}

val hashingTFTransformer = new HashingTF().setInputCol("filteredWordsFeatureVectors").setOutputCol("tfWordsFeatureVectors").setNumFeatures(1000)

val tfWordsFeatureVectorsDF = hashingTFTransformer.transform(filteredWordsFeatureVectorsDF)

val idfEstimator = new IDF().setInputCol("tfWordsFeatureVectors").setOutputCol("tfIdfWordsFeatureVectors")

val idfModelTransformer = idfEstimator.fit(tfWordsFeatureVectorsDF)

val tfIdfWordsFeatureVectorsDF = idfModelTransformer.transform(tfWordsFeatureVectorsDF)

tfIdfWordsFeatureVectorsDF.select("name", "bio", "tfIdfWordsFeatureVectors").show()

paragraphs.title: Count Featurizer - Words
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.CountVectorizer
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.CountVectorizerModel

// fit a CountVectorizerModel from the corpus
val countWordsVectorizerEstimator = new CountVectorizer()
  .setInputCol("filteredWordsFeatureVectors")
  .setOutputCol("countWordsFeatureVectors")
  .setMinDF(2) // a term must appear in more or equal to 2 documents to be included in the vocabulary

val countWordsVectorizerModelTransformer = countWordsVectorizerEstimator.fit(filteredWordsFeatureVectorsDF)

val countWordsFeatureVectorsDF = countWordsVectorizerModelTransformer.transform(filteredWordsFeatureVectorsDF).select("name", "bio", "countWordsFeatureVectors")

countWordsFeatureVectorsDF.show()
